ng with the latest science, Porder takes us deep into the Amazon, across fresh lava flows in Hawaii, and to the cornfields of the American Midwest to illuminate a potential path to sustainability, informed by the constraints imposed by life’s essential elements and the four-billion-year history of life on Earth.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aCivilization. 0aEcology. 0aEvolution (Biology). 0aLifexOrigin. 7aSCIENCE / Environmental Science (see also Chemistry / Environmental).2bisacsh  aAir conditioning.  aAntibiotics.  aBacteria.  aBiogeochemistry.  aBuilding insulation.  aBushel.  aCafeteria.  aCalcium.  aCarbonic acid.  aClimate change.  aComputer program.  aCooling.  aCowpea.  aCyanobacteria.  aDeforestation.  aEarly Earth.  aEcosystem.  aElectricity.  aElectrification.  aEnergy development.  aEnvironmental issue.  aEnzyme.  aEvolutionary biology.  aFertilizer.  aFossil fuel.  aFungus.  aGlobal Carbon Project.  aGovernment agency.  aGreenhouse gas.  aHarold Urey.  aHeat pump.  aIce core.  aInternational Energy Agency.  aKilauea.  aLaser scanning.  aLava tube.  aLeghemoglobin.  aLife.  aLongevity.  aMicroscope.  aMountain range.  aNewspaper.  aNitrogen fixation.  aNitrogen.  aNitrogenase (flavodoxin).  aNitrogenase.  aNuclear power.  aNutrient.  aOrganism.  aOxygen.  aPhosphorus.  aPhotosynthesis.  aPhotovoltaic system.  aPopulation growth.  aPower supply.  aPublication.  aRain.  aRefrigerant.  aSea surface temperature.  aShortage.  aSoil.  aSolar thermal energy.  aSubaru.  aTest tube.  aThermometer.  aTypes of volcanic eruptions.  aUncertainty.  aWavelength.  aX-ray.  aYear.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz9783111319